@startuml

title LillyTrack - Complete Attribution & Active User Flow

start

== STEP 1: Campaign Setup ==

:Marketer creates campaign in dashboard;

note right
  Config:
  - Name + auto-generated slug
  - iOS App Store URL
  - Android Play Store URL
  - Fallback URL (desktop/other)
  - Metadata: source + topic
  - (Optional) Deep Link:
    iosScheme, androidPackage, deepLinkPath
end note

:System generates tracking link
**https://...onrender.com/c/{slug}**;

:Link distributed in ads (social, email, web);

== STEP 2: Click & Redirect ==

:User taps tracking link on phone;

:Server receives **GET /c/{slug}**;

note right
  HTTP headers provide:
  - IP (x-forwarded-for)
  - User-Agent (browser string)
end note

if (isPrefetchOrBot?) then (YES)
  note right
    Detected & skipped:
    - Prefetch headers (Purpose/Sec-Purpose)
    - Social unfurlers (Slack/Twitter/FB)
    - Email scanners (Outlook SafeLinks)
    - CLI tools (curl/wget/Python-requests)
    - Short UAs (< 10 chars)
  end note
  :Skip click recording;
else (NO - Real user)

  :Parse UA -> type + model;
  note right
    "Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 10; K) Chrome/148"
    -> type="android", model="K"
  end note

  :Fingerprint = SHA256("IP|type|model");
  note right
    "203.0.113.42|android|k" -> "cf9bdfe0..."
  end note

  if (Same fingerprint + campaign within 10s?) then (Duplicate)
    :Skip recording (pg_advisory_xact_lock);
  else (New click)
    :Save click record;
    note right
      fingerprint, campaign_id, IP, UA,
      device, timestamp, expires=now+24h,
      consumed=false
    end note
    :Increment campaign click_count;
  endif

endif

if (Deep link configured?) then (YES)

  switch (Device type)
  case (iOS)
    :HTML tries **{iosScheme}://{path}**
    Falls back to App Store (1.5s);
  case (Android)
    :HTML tries **intent://{path}** URI
    Falls back to Play Store (2s);
  case (Other)
    :302 redirect -> fallback URL;
    stop
  endswitch

else (NO deep link)

  switch (Device type)
  case (iOS)
    :302 redirect -> App Store URL;
  case (Android)
    :302 redirect -> Play Store URL;
  case (Other)
    :302 redirect -> fallback URL;
    stop
  endswitch

endif

:User installs (or already has) the app;

== STEP 3: Attribution Match ==

:User opens the app;

:App sends **POST /api/v1/attribution/match**
Body: { "bundleId": "com.lilly.myapp" };

note right
  Native HTTP client sends IP + UA
  automatically in request headers
end note

#LightYellow:Detect platform from native User-Agent;

note right
  **Native SDK UA Detection:**

  **CFNetwork + Darwin** -> type = "ios"
  e.g. "MyApp/1 CFNetwork/3860 Darwin/25.5"

  **OkHttp** -> type = "android", model = "K"
  e.g. "okhttp/4.12.0"
  (model normalized to match Chrome UA Reduction)

  **Dalvik** -> type = "android"
  e.g. "Dalvik/2.1.0 (Android 16; Pixel 8)"
end note

#LightYellow:Generate fingerprint SHA256("IP|type|model");

note right
  OkHttp: SHA256("203.0.113.42|android|k")
  = "cf9bdfe0..." (matches Chrome click!)

  CFNetwork: SHA256("203.0.113.42|ios|unknown")
  (won't match Safari's "iphone" model
   -> loose fallback handles this)
end note

:**LAYER 1** - Search clicks by exact fingerprint hash;

if (Exact match?) then (Found clicks)
else (No exact match)

  :**LAYER 2** - Fallback: search by IP + device type;
  note right
    SQL: WHERE ip = ? AND device = ?
    Handles model mismatch:
    - Safari "iPhone" vs CFNetwork "unknown"
    - Firefox "Pixel 8" vs OkHttp "K"
  end note

endif

if (Any clicks found?) then (YES)

  :Filter: unconsumed + not expired + before now;

  if (Valid clicks remain?) then (YES)
    :Pick most recent valid click;
    note right
      Confidence by time gap:
      < 1h = "high"
      1-6h = "medium"
      6-24h = "low"
    end note
    :Mark click **consumed = true** (one-shot);
    :Increment campaign install_count;
    #CCFFCC:Return { matched: true, attribution: {
      campaignName, metadata, confidence } }
    Record as **NON-ORGANIC**;
  else (All expired/consumed)
    #FFCCCC:Return { matched: false }
    Record as **ORGANIC**;
  endif

else (NO clicks found at all)
  #FFCCCC:Return { matched: false, attribution: null }
  Record as **ORGANIC**;
endif

== STEP 4: Active User Tracking ==

:Record daily app launch;

note right
  Per fingerprint per calendar day:
  - **is_organic**: true / false
  - **campaign_id**: (if non-organic)
  - **platform**: ios / android / other
  - **bundle_id**: "com.lilly.myapp"
  - **launched_at**: timestamp
end note

if (Fingerprint already recorded today?) then (YES)
  if (Existing=ORGANIC, new=NON-ORGANIC?) then (YES)
    #LightBlue:**UPGRADE** record to non-organic;
    note right
      User launched organically first,
      then got campaign-matched later
      -> retroactively attributed
    end note
  else (No change needed)
    :Skip (max 1 record per device per day);
  endif
else (First launch today)
  :Insert new launch record;
endif

:Auto-purge records older than 30 days;

== Dashboard ==

note right
  **Home Page** (filter by platform + bundleId):
  - Total Active Users (30-day unique)
  - Non-Organic / Organic counts
  - Daily stacked bar charts

  **GET /api/v1/stats/apps** returns:
  {
    apps: [{ platform, bundleId }...],
    platforms: ["android", "ios"]
  }
  - platforms = ALL (even without bundleId)
  - apps = only entries WITH bundleId
end note

stop

@enduml
